        <bioghist id="ref46">
            <head>Administrative History</head>
            <p>For the film 
                <title render="italic">American Artifact</title>, director Merle Becker crossed the country interviewing rock poster artists from different eras to discover that America is currently in the midst of a 21st century "rock poster art movement," where thousands of artists around the country are doing silk screened rock poster art inspired by their local scene, the music of the time, and the spirit of an era.</p>
            <p>This film, which includes interviews with over 30 artists, takes the viewer through the different decades and incarnations of this art form, and spends time with, arguably, some of the finest artists of this genre, talking about what inspired their truly American works of art.</p>
            <p>The film features: Mark Arminski, Julie Belcher, Leia Bell, Kevin Bradley, Art Chantry, COOP, Mat Daly, Ron Donovan, EMEK, Gary Grimshaw, Justin Hampton, Derek Hess, Paul Imagine, Frank Kozik, Lindsey Kuhn, Dennis Loren, Mike Martin, Tara McPherson, Stanley Mouse, Victor Moscoso, Jim Pollock, Print Mafia, Jermaine Rogers, Jay Ryan, Scrojo, Chris Shaw, Jim Sherraden &amp; Hatch Show Print, David Singer, Chuck Sperry, Winston Smith, Stainboy, Randy Tuten, Steve Walters, and Jeff Wood.</p>
            <p>Producer/director Merle Becker is a 17+ year veteran of film and television. Credits include 
                <title render="italic">CBS Tony Awards</title>, 
                <title render="italic">Beavis &amp; Butt-Head</title>, Comedy Central's 
                <title render="italic">Tough Crowd With Colin Quinn</title>, and MTV's 
                <title render="italic">Total Request Live</title>. She has also worked on several feature films, including 
                <title render="italic">Rising Low</title> (with Warren Haynes and Phil Lesh).</p>
        </bioghist>
        <custodhist id="ref4">
            <head>Custodial History</head>
            <p>The 
                <title render="italic">American Artifact</title> Collection was received by the Rock and Roll Hall of Fame and Museum, Inc. as a gift from Merle Becker of Freakfilms, Inc. on January 12, 2010.</p>
        </custodhist>
        <separatedmaterial id="ref49">
            <head>Separated Materials</head>
            <p>Two copies of 
                <title render="italic">American Artifact: The Rise of American Rock Poster</title>, the deluxe double DVD, have been transferred to the library collection. Please search for the "American Artifact Collection" in the library catalog for a list of donated titles. If you are unable to find what you are looking for, consult the Library and Archives staff to ensure these materials are available.</p>
        </separatedmaterial>
